messages.message: Hey Team, AXA-UK is reporting that they are not able to open the review link for app-runs for randomly submitted input emails(with pdfs and/or xlxs as attachment). We see a error in console log of course when the page breaks. What we figured further was, almost all of these runs that do not load, had xlxs file as email file attachment. Others, with just pdf as attachment to the input email file are loading well in review. Another observation from the team, this was working last week. So may be something changed lately?

• i see from the har file that this is https://axa-uk.aihub.instabase.com/review/a61e8a70-bfbe-4e68-8510-e3e904d61039
• i have access to this environment, so i'm able to open this page
• i clicked on the line with the error and added a breakpoint
    ◦ see debugging process in https://instabase.zoom.us/clips/share/QTZ4ogs8RlCeEE9pWGEAgQ, Passcode: &CF!K30b
• the issue is on this line (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/e7153a7/webserver/shared/src/js/webpacked/lib/src/IBComponents/SheetViewer/SheetViewer.tsx#L180), which was added in this PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/70966) by @Veera 
    ◦ these changes were introduced in 25.24, so it makes sense that this broke after 25.24 was pushed to axa-uk.aihub.instabase.com (http://axa-uk.aihub.instabase.com) on Monday
    ◦ @Veera it's possible that `rawData[0]` is an empty array -> your code needs to handle this case
fyi @Balaram
@Veera can you check and help to fix this?
yes, I checking on this.
@vp can you let us know on the urgency for the fix?

```Hi Vikas,

Thanks to these errors, the AXA team are unable to open the links and create Ground Truths. We are supposed to finish this project in 2 weeks and this issue is a blocker for accuracy calculations and any prompt iterations. So the impact is high :)

Regards,
Supreeth T
Customer Engagement Manager, Instabase```
@vp Could you please share the sample doc that reproduces the issue so we can investigate and implement a fix.
@vp @supreeth.t can you help here?
I have asked axa team, but i doubt they will share the prod doc
whether someone from our team can help? Screen share?
Yes yes, I will patch with Prasad
He seems to be away
@vp following up on the above request
Prasad said, it has pii data, so he is checking with team
Asked him for demo
https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-4533 @Veera

@vp The field (LLM) is returning `"No value found."` and the cleaner function processes it as an empty list, which is causing the failure. To unblock them for now, they can proceed without the cleaner function applied to the field.

cleaning function is supposed to return empty in such situation, what value we expecting when cleaning function is not in the middle and no value found is returned? Will it then handle correctly? Reason am asking is, not sure at how many places and for how many app, they might have to change that
We are adding a fix to address this. In the meantime, to unblock the team can try the work around
yeah, I have let them know, see if they agree
